   "source": [
    "### Machine learning\n",
    "    machine learning enables computers to learn from data, identify patterns,\n",
    "    and make decisions with minimal human intervention instead of relying on explicit programming."
   ],
   "id": "9710913adeb0756f"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "<h5> Machine learning algorithms:</h5>\n",
    "    1: Supervised learning\n",
    "    2: Unsupervised learning"
   ],
   "id": "d0b202756e0865d"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "<h5>Supervised learning:</h5>\n",
    "   In this process, the algorithm is trained on a dataset containing input-output pairs. The \"supervision\" comes from the fact that the correct answers (labels) are provided during training. The model iteratively adjusts its internal parameters to minimize the difference between its predictions and the actual labels, effectively learning the underlying relationship between the data features and the target outcome."
   ],
   "id": "fd89cba2c7871c42",
   "outputs": []
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "### Regression model:\n",
    "     This involves predicting a continuous numerical value. Instead of categories, the output is a quantity. Common examples include predicting house prices based on features like size and location, forecasting stock market trends, or estimating temperature based on weather data.\n"
   ],
   "id": "f1397e41f10d623b",
   "outputs": []
  },
